name: Simeon
text:
Sparking young minds into the wonderful world of science!
Sci-Quest makes science fun for people young and old, with interactive experiments and great exhibits. The friendly staff are always there to help.
When I was young, I always loved to see what was new every visit. From growing DNA and making it visible to dissecting snakes.  Sci-Quest brings it all!

name: Fordtrck302
text: While not all together bad, a good amount of the exhibits did not function either all together or were partially broke. From the looks this has been a long standing problem. For the price their asking I wouldn't go again.

name: Jason Tynes
text: Very good overall. Some broken exhibits but young kids love it! Hopefully it's better when they move from Calhoun community college.

name: Shawn Danielle FitzPatrick
text: Great idea but horrible execution. Most of the exhibits are not working or missing parts. My children enjoyed it but pretty sure they could of had as much fun playing at mcdonalds for free.

name: Justin Prater
text: A very very cool attraction for younger kids and they have fun summer camps. But they never really add any new exhibits

name: a Google User
text: It amazes me Sciquest can get people to pay for their museum. It is okay. Nothing great. It is WAAAAYYY overpriced for what it is. Exhibits feel grubby and half of them don't function correctly. Next time I'll save my money.

text: Great place but 25% of the exhibits are broken. My kids still love it.

text: My daughter loved her visit to Sci-Quest!

text: Definitely recommend to anyone traveling or in the area. My girlfriend and I loved it and got a ton of fun, goofy, cute pictures! text: I absolutely loved this place!!!! I can’t wait to go back with more friends!!!! There are so many cool backgrounds and props!!! Megan was super friendly and helpful! I had the best time!!!! text: this place was so much fun! as soon as my boyfriend and i walked in we were immediately greeted by tracy i believe was her name! she was super helpful and kind! we will never forget this place! we also got some great shots that will last a lifetime :)

name: Mandie McArty Gosa
text: Wow! A bit pricey, but what a gem when you need a break from the sun! Generally, I would have not thought twice about a "Selphie Museum", however, coming across a few reviews during my search for things to do in Gulf Shores, we decided to give it a shot...and we were NOT disappointed! We could have stayed for HOURS if we allowed ourselves. We had 3 adults with two 12 yr old boys, one 10 yr old boy, and an 8 yr old girl. We ALL had a blast!!

name: Mallorie Brunswig
text: My boyfriend and I went and we had an amazing time!!! There are so many different places to take pictures and cool background. Good for all ages. I definitely would go back if I lived closer. Megan (the manager) was happy to help with anything we needed and gave us great tips. I definitely recommend!

name: Jasmine Morley
text: This place is so much fun! Worth the price and definitely would go back!

name: Morgan Daniels
text: My family had so much fun!!! Even if you don’t want to be in the photos you can take them of your kids , spouse , friends for free!! Price isn’t bad if you want to be in the photos ... they even did a bonus family picture at the end of your tour . All the props were great !!!! The lighting was Amazing! Be on the lookout for the cutest dog in the world, he enjoyed being a prop in our photos as well ! All around my whole family loved it .

name: Amber Morris
text: Awesome little adventure with the kids. We saw it while riding through The Wharf, and it turned out to be really fun! I highly recommend as something to engage all ages and I'd definitely do it again.

text: We had so much fun at this place. Stopped here while on vacation in Gulf Shores. They had so many unique sets to take pictures in. Owner was very friendly and we even got pictures with his dog. The girl at the front was helpful and great with the kids. This was definitely money well spent!

name: Melanie Berman
text: This place was so much fun! It’s great to go in the morning when no one is there. Meagan was very helpful and we had a great time.

Regret not asking her name, but the blonde girl working the desk was incredibly friendly and helpful, and went out of her way to show us around and give us good tips. An experience I will never forget!

This was such a fun experience! The owner and the workers were so sweet and helpful. We had so much fun, and each set was really well done! Our photos turned out great!!!
I would say though my only complaint was that, while each set had a ringlight, they didn’t all have a way to hold the phone up for you. Not a big deal tho!

The owner came out and spoke to us a few times and the staff was beyond sweet. Well worth the money and could see coming back to enjoy at a later date. My daughter is already asking when she can bring her friends.
